##Global outbreak: STATE OF EMERGENCY IN 3 U.S. states, more than 6,000 confirmed cases in South Korea

Micro Signal China Business Journal

Function introduction, grow in step with Chinese enterprises, talk with business leaders, spread business ideals, serve business people, "China Business News" control of the absolute voice of Chinese business.

In the past day, more than 15,000 cases have been confirmed outside China, with new cases in South Korea, Italy, Iran and other countries continuing to rise as the epidemic spread.

WHO: inadequate preparedness for new coronary pneumonia in some countries

On March 5, local time, the World Health Organization Organization in Geneva to hold a regular briefing on the new pneumonia epidemic, the global situation. Who director-general Tan Desai said it was a matter of concern that some countries were not paying enough attention to the disease and were not prepared for it to spread to more countries, especially those with weak health systems.

But tandser also pointed out that 115 countries have not reported any new cases of pneumonia, 21 countries only one case. In the past 14 days, five countries with new cases of coronary pneumonia have not reported additional cases. The experience of these countries and China shows that the epidemic is not irreversible. Tan Desai calls for rapid action by governments in a coordinated effort across all sectors to tackle the disease, which is a threat to all countries.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
More than 6,000 cases have been confirmed in Khanh Son, which has been designated as a special management area for infectious diseases

As of 4:00 pm on the 5th, 322 new cases of pneumonia had been confirmed in South Korea, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 6088.

The South Korean government announced on the 5th that it had decided to list North Gyeongsang Province as a special management area for infectious diseases in view of the recent increase in new cases of pneumonia in the city, mainly in Gyeongsan. South Korea said that the city of Khanh Son has now emerged second-generation infection and small-scale cluster infection, the need to focus on community infection before further spread of measures to curb the spread of the epidemic to other areas. Gyeongsan is located in the south of North Gyeongsang Province, its west and south with the city of Daegu and Gyeongsang North Road Clearance County border.

Medical workers transfer patients at North University Hospital in Daegu, South Korea, March 4,2010. Xinhua News Agency (photo by Li Xianghao)

Previously, due to the emergence of large-scale clusters of infection, Daegu city and North Gyeongsang Kyungyeongdo county on February 21 was designated by the South Korean government as a special management area for infectious diseases.

A total of 3,858 cases have been confirmed in Italy, and the government has allocated 7.5 billion euros to deal with the epidemic

At 18:00 local time on March 5, Angelo David Borrelli, head of Italy's Civil Defence Department and Commissioner of the New Coronavirus Emergency Response Committee, said at a regular press conference on the outbreak that there were 3,296 cases of new coronavirus infection pneumonia in Italy, there were 590 more cases than the previous day, 148 deaths, 41 more cases than the previous day, 414 cured cases, 138 more cases than the previous day. A total of 3,858 new cases of pneumonia have been confirmed in the country.

Two cases were reported for the first time in the northwestern Italian Aosta Valley of region of France on Friday, marking the first confirmed cases in all 20 regions of the country.

On the same day, Italian Prime Minister Contes announced that the government had allocated 7.5 billion euros to support families and businesses in the country to deal with the emergency caused by the outbreak.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Italian medics work in tents set up outside a hospital in Brescia. Photo / Xinhua

A total of 3,513 schools in Iran will be closed until 20 days

According to the latest news from the Ministry of Health, 591 new cases of pneumonia and 15 new deaths were confirmed in Iran on the 5th local time. As of noon that day, a total of 3,513 new cases of pneumonia had been confirmed in Iran, of which 739 had recovered and 107 had died.

Shaykh al-Islām, international affairs adviser to the Speaker of the Iranian parliament, has died of new pneumonia, the Tasnim News Agency reported Friday.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Iran's health minister said two important decisions had been made: one to set up 300,000 outbreak investigation teams, and the other to close all schools, universities and educational institutions until March 20.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A woman wears a mask as she travels in Tehran, Iran, on March 2.

Another cruise ship! There's been an outbreak on the U.S.S. Princess

California health officials said Thursday that the first death in the state that day had been aboard the "Supreme Princess" cruise ship. Currently, the ship is en route to San Francisco, the ship is said to have 21 people have symptoms of infection. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention has asked 62 passengers who had contact with the patient to stay in their rooms and wait for tests. The California government has ordered the ship off-limits and will send emergency crews to board and inspect the ship.

The ship is stuck at sea with more than 3,000 passengers and crew. Two passengers who had travelled on the cruise ship had been diagnosed with new pneumonia, and one died. At present, local health officials have begun to test the ship's personnel.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Royal Princess and the Diamond Princess are part of Carnival group, the world's largest holiday company. The group is based in Florida.

The report says there are at least 197 confirmed cases in the United States

On March 5, the CNN reported the first confirmed case of a new coronavirus infection in Tennessee.

On the afternoon of March 5, local time, List of Governors of New York Como held a press conference, said the same day in New York confirmed many new cases of coronavirus infection, New York state has now confirmed cases of 22 cases.

There are at least 197 confirmed cases in the United States, according to data compiled by John  Johan's Johns Hopkins University.

The Governor of California declared a state of emergency Thursday due to the threat of a new coronavirus. California is now the third state to declare a state of emergency.

On March 5, the U.S. Senate passed an $8.3 billion emergency funding bill to help fight the new outbreak of pneumonia. The bill is now in the hands of President Donald Trump, who is expected to sign it soon.

Affected by the continuous rise in new cases of coronavirus infection in the United States, the U.S. stock market fell sharply on the 5th local time and closed the same day, the Dow Jones Industrial Average, the Nasdaq composite and the S & P 500 all fell more than 3 percent, with the Dow Jones Industrial Average down nearly 1,000 points, or 3.6 percent.

Confirmed cases in Germany rose to 500 and in France to 423

According to the "European Times" German local time published statistics at 17:00 on March 5, as of March 5,17:00, Germany has a total of 500 confirmed cases of new pneumonia.

Local time on the evening of March 5, the French Ministry of Health, the latest report, as of that day, France, a total of 423 confirmed cases of new pneumonia, an increase of 138 cases from the previous day, including 23 in critical condition. Three new deaths were recorded on 5 March, bringing the total to 7.

There have been more than 100 confirmed cases in many countries

Switzerland: As of 6:00 local time on the 5th, Switzerland confirmed 111 cases of new coronary pneumonia, of which one died and three were cured.

Singapore: A total of 117 new cases of Ministry of Health pneumonia were confirmed in the evening of May 5. A total of 81 patients were discharged from the hospital, and 7 were in critical condition.

UK: According to the latest figures released by the UK Disease Control and Prevention Department on the 5th, 29 new cases of coronavirus infection in the UK, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 116. In reading, near London, an elderly patient locally infected with the new coronavirus died. It is also the first death in the UK.

First confirmed case of new coronary pneumonia in South Africa

South Africa has found its first case of a new coronavirus positive, health minister Zvehli Mukaz said in a statement on March 5, local media reported. For now, relatives and other contacts will also be quarantined and tested. The patient is a 38-year-old man who was diagnosed after returning from Italy to South Africa.
